[normal]have 
[normal]been 
[normal]taken in recent years to encourage better joint working between the services. In the 2010 S
[normal]pending 
[normal]R
[normal]eview
[normal] 
[normal]the Department 
[normal]introduced a transfer from the NHS to social care, to be used on social 
[normal]care with a health benefit, and gave the NHS up to £300
[normal] 
[normal]m
[normal]illion
[normal] a year to deliver reablement services.
[normal]70
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]And for 
[normal]20
[normal]15
[normal]–16
[normal] 
[normal]the Department 
[normal]is 
[normal]going much further by introducing a £3.8
[normal] 
[normal]b
[normal]illio
[normal]n pooled budget for health and social care. This will break new ground i
[normal]n driving closer integration, by bring CCGs and local authorities together to make real spending decisions and consider the impact on all services.
[normal]71
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Although some 
[normal]local authorities 
[normal]have reduced their expenditure on adult social care, there is no 
[normal]conclusive 
[normal]evidence that this is having an impact on the NHS. In fact, 
[normal]a
[normal] 
[normal]key 
[normal]indicator 
[normal]the Department monitors 
[normal]says the opposite: the number of delayed transfers attributed to social care has been falling.
[normal] However, CCGs are (as of August 2013) forecasting an overspen
[normal]d of £40 million on NHS continuing healthcare in 2013–14, which may indicate that social care pressures are having 
[normal]some
[normal] knock-on impact on the NHS.
[normal]2.3[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The ability of local authorities to make the necessary efficiency savings[bold]72
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]In 
[normal]both 
