[normal]127
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]The difficulty of allocating 
[normal]resources is therefore more acute than it has been in the previous ten years. Of the £2.5
[normal] 
[normal]b
[normal]illio
[normal]n available, demand pressures consume £1.8
[normal] 
[normal]b
[normal]illio
[normal]n, even after an assumption that demand growth will be lower than in recent years due to the transformational a
[normal]ctivities being undertaken as part of the NHS
[normal] 
[normal]QIPP challenge.
[normal]128
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]At the same time as demand is growing, the NHS must improve its services, responding to the challenge set by the Francis report into Mid Staffordshire, the Keogh Review into hospital mortality 
[normal]and the Berwick review on patient safety.  NHS England welcomes the focus on growing a culture which puts patients first, engages and empowers patients and carers, supports transparency and learning and takes responsibility for poor care. This is all under
[normal]pinned by having the right staff with the right skills and knowledge.
[normal]129
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Therefore, i
[normal]mprovements in workforce productivity are key to helping deliver the 
[normal]service improvements and 
[normal]efficiency savings in this, and the next, 
[normal]s
[normal]pending 
[normal]r
[normal]ound period. So far, workfor
[normal]ce productivity gains have contributed 12
[normal]%
[normal] of the total savings made in 2011
[normal]–12
[normal] and 2012
[normal]–13
[normal], compared 
[normal]with
[normal] 23
[normal]%
[normal] which has come from pay restraint. The workforce productivity share of total savings is expected to grow to 26
[normal]% 
[normal]in 2013
[normal]–14
[normal] and 201
[normal]4
[normal]–15
[normal].
[normal]130
[normal]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Despite i
[normal]mproved productivity performance in the last two years, there still exists wide labour productivity variation at 
[normal]provider
[normal] 
[normal]level.
[normal] 
[normal]Levelling up performance as well as shifting the average 
[normal]provider
[normal] performance upwards will help achieve the workforce pr
[normal]oductiv
[normal]ity gains that are need
[normal]ed.
[normal] 
[normal]However, while much of this improvement can be achieved through concerted action by clinicians and managers, a substantial proportion will require transformational change in the provider land
[normal]s
[normal]cape to remove structural inefficienc
[normal]ies
[normal].
